news.title: Uttar Pradesh's first plant to convert construction waste into bricks starts operations
news.para: Constructed at a cost of over Rs 5.5 crores, the plant has the capacity of handling 100 metric tonnes (MT) of construction waste per day.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government forms SIT to probe fraudulent property registrations
news.para: The SIT, headed by an ex-IAS officer, will investigate various malpractices such as fraudulent property registrations and impersonations.

news.title: How 'waterfall implosion' may help bring down Supertech twin towers
news.para: Apex and Ceyane, the twin residential towers built by Supertech, were held illegal by the Supreme Court, which had in an order passed on August 31 this year upheld the Allahabad high court’s directions to bring down both towers.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body draws up plan to raze 20,000 illegal buildings
news.para: The expense of demolishing an illegal structure will be recovered from the property holder or its owner by billing the cost of razing to the property tax or showing it as a pending due to the 7/12 extract of the property.

news.title: Hyderabad: 13,000 LED lights bring glow to outer ring road
news.para: While in the first phase, LED lighting was done between Gachibowli and Shamshabad covering a distance of 22 km three years ago, LED lighting for the balance 136 km was completed now.

news.title: Get 2% off in property tax for EV charging stations in Kolhapur
news.para: KMC’s administrator Kadambari Balkawade signed the administrative order to implement the decision on Wednesday. Kolhapur district guardian minister Satej Patil made the announcement regarding the civic body’s decision on Thursday.

news.title: Punjab CM lays the foundation stone of Atal Apartments
news.para: The chief minister said that this project is being constructed by Ludhiana Improvement Trust (LIT) under “100 percent self financing scheme” and would have 12-storeyed 336 HIG and 240 MIG flats.

news.title: Gurugram: Five DLF-3 properties fined for violating building norms
news.para: The enforcement wing of the department of town and country planning (DTCP) also recommended that approvals for the properties be withdrawn if they fail to comply with the tribunal’s guidelines within seven days.

news.title: Allahabad HC dismisses petition alleging illegal construction by Saya Homes
news.para: In the petition, Sun Tower Residents Welfare Association had alleged that the Ghaziabad Development Authority and builder were not legally conducting the construction of the Indirapuram’s residential project SAYA Gold Avenue.

news.title: Commercial plots on offer near Jewar airport site
news.para: YEIDA has expedited work on a slew of schemes starting with the commercial and industrial plot schemes, even as final touches are being given to around 450 residential plot scheme proposed in Sector 16 of YEIDA.

news.title: Saint Gobain wants to triple revenues to Rs 30,000 crore in 10 years
news.para: Saint Gobain’s plaster boards, construction chemicals that are used as additives in ready mix concrete, fasad, insulators and ceilings are witnessing strong demand from the construction sector.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing's promoter sells 11.9% stake to make it professionally managed firm
news.para: "With this sale, I and my promoter companies now own 9.8 per cent of the company. I intend to hold these shares and participate in the future growth story of the company," Indiabulls Housing Finance quoted Gehlaut as saying in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Mumbai: Adani, L&T and Naman Developers bid for Motilal Nagar redevelopment
news.para: Two top developers, Godrej Properties and Bengaluru-based Prestige Group, formally protested and wrote to Mhada about a controversial clause in the tender which makes most builders ineligible for the huge contract.

news.title: Haryana RERA asks police to produce senior management of Sepset Properties & Supertech
news.para: According to K K Khandelwal, both the companies have not be responding to notices of the authority and not complying with the orders issued by it.

news.title: New York City moves to stop new buildings from using natural gas
news.para: If Democratic Mayor Bill de Blasio signs the measure, as expected, most construction projects submitted for approval after 2027 would have to use something other than gas or oil - such as electricity - for heating, hot water and cooking. Some smaller buildings would have to comply as early as 2024.
